<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-10-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="194" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Conger</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-10-28"><hi rend="italic">October 28,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 580.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 1077, of August 29 last, and to inform you that an item for $8,000,
                            for the erection of a suitable building for the accommodation of the ten
                            student interpreters, and another for $1,000 for the payment of the
                            yearly cost of their tuition, have been inserted in the estimates for
                            the next fiscal year.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>